														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1683153">
									

<p>I read it a couple of times to make sure I wasn't missing something, and maybe I still am, but there seems to be a pretty big basic error. Correct me if I'm wrong, but&#8230;</p>
<p>These frat boys go to our reality the night before the guy's speech (or whenever, if it's time travel too I guess It's irrelevant) and basically insert the entire Roman culture/empire, profoundly altering our proceeding timeline. This then makes the head guys speech ridiculously inaccurate, which the dean, and entire audience, instantly realize. So my question is; why doesn't this guy, whose job is solely to study other realities, have this new timeline retconned into his head like apparently everyone else?</p>
<p>Again, if I'm missing something obvious, I apologize.</p>

